  "narrative": {
    "intro": "FY2026 to date, federal obligations awarded through 8(a) Business Development set-asides total $5.7B across 7,851 awards with an average award size of $727K. Obligations are down 58.3% year over year. The Department of Defense accounts for the largest share of activity at $2.8B, followed by the Department of Health and Human Services at $504M and the Department of Homeland Security at $474M. Industry concentration is strongest in IT and professional services: Computer Systems Design Services leads at $714M, Other Computer Related Services is next at $579M, and Facilities Support Services follows at $570M. FY26 to date totals sit below recent fiscal years, which ranged from $11.3B in FY21 up to $15.1B in FY24 and $13.7B in FY25. The top vendors in FY2026 to date include AKIMA FACILITIES OPERATIONS LLC at $83.6M, CHEROKEE NATION STRATEGIC PROGRAMS, L.L.C. at $72.2M, and ASRC FEDERAL TECHNOLOGY SOLUTIONS, LLC at $61.6M. These figures reflect obligations only and represent fiscal year to date totals.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How did FY2026 to date obligations compare with prior years?",
        "body": "FY2026 to date obligations total $5.7B, which is lower than each of the prior five fiscal years listed. FY21 obligations were $11.3B, FY22 were $12.2B, FY23 were $14.1B, FY24 were $15.1B, and FY25 were $13.7B. Obligations are down 58.3% year over year, indicating a sizable decrease in 8(a) set-aside spending through the fiscal year to date."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Where are FY2026 to date obligations concentrated by agency and industry?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense accounts for the largest portion of FY2026 to date obligations at $2.8B, followed by the Department of Health and Human Services at $504M and the Department of Homeland Security at $474M. Industry concentration is led by Computer Systems Design Services at $714M, Other Computer Related Services at $579M, and Facilities Support Services at $570M. The top ten industries together show a focus on IT, engineering, facilities, and professional services."
      }
    ]
  },
